{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "On the OOD track, they used a domain-adaptive pre-training technique which reduced MSE.",
    "They also provided zero-shot results on the OOD track.• The ZevoMOS system (T01) [136] was based on SSL-MOS, but they used two SSL inputs and an ASR confidence score.",
    "Moreover, the SSL models were first fine-tuned on the FoR dataset [137] to classify natural and synthetic speech, then finetuned on the BVCC dataset.• The system by JAIST (T08) [138] was based on MOSA-Net with two key concepts: an auditory filterbank and temporal modulation.",
    "A temporal modulation feature on the gammatone filterbank (TMGF) was concatenated with the HuBERT features.",
    "They showed that this method could improve prediction on utterances with a low MOS.• The system from NICT (T11) [139] ranked first in LCC, SRCC, and KTAU in both the main track system level metrics and the OOD track utterance level metrics."
  ],
